2.2 Shift and difference asymmetry functions

Change in 6-min walking test (6MWT) distance between 0 and 12 months (N = 75). On panels A and C, the error bars over the points are the standard deviations around the means. On panels D and F, the error bars are 95% confidence intervals non corrected for multiple comparisons. On panel E, the black line depicts the identity line. If any, significant results (based on adjusted p-values) in the shift (panel C) and difference asymmetry (panel F) functions are highlighted using thick red circles. A small pseudo-random movement has been added horizontally and vertically to the raw data displayed on panel E to minimize the presence of points fully overlapped.
